	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The distinction between musician and programmer wasn't so sharp back then. There's a talk that Rob Hubbard gave where he explains how he and other musicians used to work on the C64: <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4E5oYZmQnoI#t=00m35s" class="postlink">youtube video</a>
<br />
<br />That doesn't mean they didn't use keyboards while composing tunes. And it certainly doesn't mean you can't use one. That's one of the advantages of doing music now compared to 20 years ago; you've got a lot more advanced tools available now than they had.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


